\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_4092234\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_4092234\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ciq1665702768050_2.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ciq1665702768050_2.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ciq1665702768050_2.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ciq1665702768050\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n           \n Scripting in Server Pages \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ciq1665702768050__scripting_in_server_pages_75915\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ciq1665702768050__p_d21782e1_d21783e1_d21784e1\">When scripting server pages, you need to consider the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ciq1665702768050__li_d10688e1_d10689e1_d10690e1\">Some triggers are not available in web environment. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fcj1719477302864.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fcj1719477302864.html\" title=\"Dynamic server pages (DSPs) have system triggers that are executed on the server, and client-side web triggers that are executed in the browser.\">Triggers in Dynamic Server Pages</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wif1665702767979.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wif1665702767979.html\" title=\"Static server pages have non-interactive triggers. Only the field-level detail trigger for a Button widget is interactive.\">Triggers in Static Server Pages</a>.\n            </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ciq1665702768050__li_d10691e1_d10692e1_d10693e1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Interactive ProcScript is limited and you should consider the use of fields,\n               functions, and HTML pages to pass messages and warnings to your users. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ciq1665702768050__p_d21785e1_d21786e1_d21787e1\">Some ProcScript instructions are specific for web\n               applications, such as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$webinfo</span>, which allows you to access objects\n               in a HTTP request including all web server variables. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xcq1665702683871.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xcq1665702683871.html\" title=\"Some ProcScript instructions are specific to web applications (including static server pages). There are also some that are unique to dynamic server pages. They are used to read data into the component, and generate responses to be sent to the client, and to activate ProcScript modules on the client or the server.\">ProcScript for Dynamic Server Pages</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uix1665702684801.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uix1665702684801.html\" title=\"Several ProcScript instructions are specific to web applications, and some other ProcScript instructions behave differently in web applications or are inapplicable.\">ProcScript for Static Server Pages</a>.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ciq1665702768050__li_d10694e1_d10695e1_d10696e1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Server pages have a limited lifetime and do not exist on the server between the\n               initial display and the submission of a page. This also affects the scope of\n               variables. For example, the value of a component variable is deleted after an HTTP\n               request is handled. You need to use a state management to keep the value. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ciq1665702768050__p_d21788e1_d21789e1_d21790e1\">Uniface also provides several state management\n               mechanisms. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vif1719486836379.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vif1719486836379.html\" title=\"The stateless nature of the HTTP protocol means that Uniface server pages are stateless and must explicitly implement state management using one or more of the available state management mechanisms.\">State Management Mechanisms</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ciq1665702768050__p_d21791e1_d21792e1_d21793e1\">Some triggers can be used to maintain state\n               information. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mnp1719487736673.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mnp1719487736673.html\" title=\"Maintaining state information is an important aspect of developing web applications. Uniface provides state triggers to get and set state information, and to provide pre- and post-processing.\">State Triggers</a>.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ciq1665702768050__li_d10697e1_d10698e1_d10699e1\">Operations called from a URL cannot have parameters defined in their signatures. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nzw1665702540991.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nzw1665702540991.html\" title=\"You can call operations on a static server page by extending the URL to include the operation name, or by specifying the operation in the Action URL attribute of the &lt;form&gt; element of a static server page. This provides a mechanism for sharing state information between USPs.\">Calling Operations on Static Server Pages</a>.\n            </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ciq1665702768050__li_d10700e1_d10701e1_d10702e1\">In static server pages, you can use ProcScript to build hyperlinks and other HTML code dynamically. In a complex application, you can move the user interface coding to the HTML page itself, for example, using JavaScript to define page behavior. However, in this case it is usually preferable to use dynamic server pages.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ciq1665702768050__p_d21794e1_d21795e1_d21796e1\">For more detailed information on scripting in dynamic server pages and static server pages, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ull1704691217498.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ull1704691217498.html\" title=\"Dynamic Server Pages(DSP) components define the user interface of web pages that can be incrementally and dynamically updated. They can be used in rich interactive web applications and in cross-platform mobile apps.\">Dynamic Server Pages</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"snh1704692180687.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/snh1704692180687.html\" title=\"Static Server Page (USP) components generate a complete web page every time they are activated. This makes them useful for relatively static web pages or a thin-client architecture in which all processing is done on the server. They can also be used for RESTful applications or file upload functionality.\">Static Server Pages</a> and their sub-topics.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4092234\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4092234\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Scripting in Server Pages Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Scripting in Server Pages When scripting server pages, you need to consider the following: Some triggers are not available in web environment. For more information, see Triggers in Dynamic Server Pages and Triggers in Static Server Pages . Interactive ProcScript is limited and you should consider the use of fields, functions, and HTML pages to pass messages and warnings to your users. Some ProcScript instructions are specific for web applications, such as $webinfo , which allows you to access objects in a HTTP request including all web server variables. For more information, see ProcScript for Dynamic Server Pages and ProcScript for Static Server Pages . Server pages have a limited lifetime and do not exist on the server between the initial display and the submission of a page. This also affects the scope of variables. For example, the value of a component variable is deleted after an HTTP request is handled. You need to use a state management to keep the value. Uniface also provides several state management mechanisms. For more information, see State Management Mechanisms . Some triggers can be used to maintain state information. For more information, see State Triggers . Operations called from a URL cannot have parameters defined in their signatures. For more information, see Calling Operations on Static Server Pages . In static server pages, you can use ProcScript to build hyperlinks and other HTML code dynamically. In a complex application, you can move the user interface coding to the HTML page itself, for example, using JavaScript to define page behavior. However, in this case it is usually preferable to use dynamic server pages. For more detailed information on scripting in dynamic server pages and static server pages, see Dynamic Server Pages and Static Server Pages and their sub-topics. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}